  <h1>Allergen Risks</h1>
  <p>This page provides information about common allergens and their associated risks.</p>

  <h2>Common Allergens and Risks</h2>
  <p>Individuals with allergies need to be cautious about specific allergens. Here are some common allergens and the risks they pose:</p>

  <h3>1. Peanuts</h3>
  <p>Peanut allergies can range from mild to severe. In severe cases, exposure to even trace amounts of peanuts can lead to a life-threatening reaction called anaphylaxis.</p>

  <h3>2. Tree Nuts</h3>
  <p>Tree nut allergies can cause similar reactions to peanut allergies. Common tree nuts include almonds, walnuts, and cashews.</p>

  <h3>3. Milk</h3>
  <p>Individuals with milk allergies may experience digestive symptoms, skin reactions, or respiratory issues when consuming dairy products.</p>

  <h3>4. Eggs</h3>
  <p>Egg allergies can cause skin reactions, gastrointestinal discomfort, and respiratory symptoms. People with egg allergies should avoid foods containing eggs.</p>

  <h3>5. Wheat</h3>
  <p>Wheat allergies can lead to digestive problems, skin irritation, and in some cases, anaphylaxis. People with wheat allergies need to avoid wheat-based products.</p>

  <h3>6. Soy</h3>
  <p>Soy allergies can cause a variety of symptoms, including digestive issues, skin reactions, and respiratory problems. Soy is commonly found in processed foods.</p>

  <h3>7. Fish and Shellfish</h3>
  <p>Fish and shellfish allergies can cause severe reactions, and exposure to even tiny amounts can lead to anaphylaxis. Allergic reactions can vary depending on the type of fish or shellfish.</p>

  <p>It's important for individuals with allergies to carefully read ingredient labels and avoid products that contain allergens they are sensitive to.</p>
